    "problemStatement": "Chef opened a tree-selling business this Christmas.\n\nHe bought NNN trees for AAA rupees, and then sold MMM trees for BBB rupees.\n\nWhat was his profit this Christmas? If Chef instead made a loss of XXX rupees, print −X-X−X.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first and only line of input contains 444 integers - N,A,MN, A, MN,A,M and BBB.\n\n\nOutput Format\nOutput Chef's profit this christmas.",
    "constraints": [
      "1≤M≤N≤1001 \\le M \\le N \\le 1001≤M≤N≤100",
      "100≤A≤B≤1000100 \\le A \\le B \\le 1000100≤A≤B≤1000"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
